When you have annotation with Class property and then you set it to some primitive type eg. `boolean.class` you will get GWT compilation errors in reflection cache generator: 

```
Compiling module com.kotcrab.playground.GdxDefinition
   Resolving com.kotcrab.playground.Playground.Foo
      Found type 'com.kotcrab.playground.Playground.Foo'
         [ERROR] Annotation error: cannot resolve boolean
java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: boolean
        at java.net.URLClassLoader.findClass(URLClassLoader.java:381)
[...]
         Invoking generator com.badlogic.gwtref.gen.ReflectionCacheGenerator
            [ERROR] Error invoking annotation method.
[...]
[ERROR] Line 10966: This method must return a result of type Class
```

[(full log)](https://gist.github.com/kotcrab/f4d6c7ac9041b88c2068#file-gistfile1-txt-L18-L21)

SSCCE:

```
public class AnnotationIssue extends ApplicationAdapter {
    @Override
    public void create () {
        Foo f = new Foo();
    }

    public static class Foo {
        @TestAnnotation(type = boolean.class)
        public int foo;
    }

    @Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)
    @Target(ElementType.FIELD)
    public @interface TestAnnotation {
        Class<?> type ();
    }
}
```

The sample code below generates a 3 by 3 image using the setWrap(Texture.TextureWrap.MirroredRepeat, Texture.TextureWrap.MirroredRepeat) and setRegion functions.

Problem:
- On Android, independently of the size of the source image , it works.
- On iOS, using RoboVM, the image size mut be a power of two. if the image is not a power of two, the image is shown as black.

    public class GameScreen implements Screen {

  ```
  MyGdxGame game;
  private Stage stage;

  public GameScreen(MyGdxGame aGame){
      stage = new Stage(new ScreenViewport());
      game = aGame;
      Texture imgTexture = new Texture(Gdx.files.internal("badlogic.jpg"));
      imgTexture.setWrap(Texture.TextureWrap.MirroredRepeat, Texture.TextureWrap.MirroredRepeat);
      TextureRegion imgTextureRegion = new TextureRegion(imgTexture);
      imgTextureRegion.setRegion(0,0,imgTexture.getWidth()*3,imgTexture.getHeight()*3);

      TextureRegionDrawable imgTextureRegionDrawable = new TextureRegionDrawable(imgTextureRegion);
      Image img = new Image();
      img.setDrawable(imgTextureRegionDrawable);
      img.setSize(imgTexture.getWidth()*3,imgTexture.getHeight()*3);
      stage.addActor(img);
  }

  @Override
  public void show() {

  }

  @Override
  public void render(float delta) {
      Gdx.gl.glClearColor(1, 0, 0, 1);
      Gdx.gl.glClear(GL20.GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);
      stage.act(delta);
      stage.draw();
  }

  @Override
  public void resize(int width, int height) {
      stage.getViewport().update(width, height, true);
  }

  @Override
  public void pause() {

  }

  @Override
  public void resume() {

  }

  @Override
  public void hide() {

  }

  @Override
  public void dispose() {
      stage.dispose();
  }
